<br>
btw it is NOT Massive Multiplayer    i think i read that its designed to support aroun 8 ppl or so <br>
<br>
its fairly stressful on processors   ive fooled around with my two graphics cards  16MB and 64MB and can hardly tell a diff    processor power is a must   with a 1ghz i slow down when more than 5 guys are hacking at me(yes it gets hairy in chapter 1) <br>
<br>
            ALL classes are available to ALL races  however some classes are alliance restricted    example: Bards must remain chaotic(nuetral good or evil)  monks cant be lawful else they stop leveling    and paladins must remain good and i think lawful or they stop leveling       <br>
<br>
Each race has various unique &quot;feats&quot;(skills and proficiencies) and slight stat mods                     <br>
<br>
AC is based on dex and actual AC of the armor you wear     you play from the 3rd person overhead mode(or at least i do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )    <br>
<br>
unlike Bauldur's Gate and other previous titles using AD&amp;D you hire mercenaries or henchmen instead of picking up party members    some henchmen join if u help them though(for free) you cannot mess around with their inventory to my knowledge   however u can use all the skills they have available by right clicking their portrait....  NWN also uses an elaborate &quot;examine&quot; system sort of like EQ's consider     it ranges from purple(no chance in heck) to red(dificult but posible to kill) to orange(might have to heal some but you can do it!)   yellow(same level as you   u can take em np)  blue(nothing to worry   just a flesh wound) to green(little exp  but u can slaughter em all day long)  white(why bother)<br>
<br>
Plot is slow to unravel but wha ive caught so far is a plague called The Wailing Death is killing off the city of Neverwinter....     your character works for the city militia(after completing your training) and is charged with the task of finding a cure for the plague(sounds hard and this is only chapter 1!)<br>
<br>
My character is a Elven Monk with Spirit Warrior package(nothing like a monk with swords and bows!)<br>
<br>
